'''John Barry Sines Jr''' (born October 15, 1968 in Bedford, Virginia) is an American [[country music]] singer/songwriter.

== Biography ==

John Sines Jr was born and raised in [[Bedford, Virginia]]. His father, John Sines Sr and his mother Sandra Bryant performed locally as country musicians & influenced him to begin playing music as well.  Sines learned to play guitar and started writing songs at the age of 14.  Sines started The Country Adjustment Band while in high school with his brother Sammie Sines. He has four sisters, Rhonda May Long, Brandy Sines, Crystal Sines and McKenzie Sines. He married Patricia Stinnett in 1988 and they have three children, Jonathan Sines, Zachary Sines and Savannah Sines.<ref> Nielsen Business Media, [https://books.google.com/books?id=DxUEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA83&lpg=PA83&dq=john+sines+jr+interview&source=bl&ots=_0OC2e30D9&sig=VUeTmzlhTBgwRBWFvDn0fdLcqYY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=lvXYVIHvIoHfggS7uoHgDQ&ved=0CEEQ6AEwCDgK#v=onepage&q=john%20sines%20jr%20interview&f=false "Lifeline - Country Singer Welcomes Baby"], July 21, 2001, online at Billboard Magazine</ref> Sines currently performs as a Christian artist, advocating the cause of Christ. [http://www.wprz.org/files/August%202014%20Highlights.pdf]

== Musical career ==

=== 1984:  ''The Country Adjustment Band'' ===

In April, 1984 he founded The Country Adjustment Band in [[Goode, Virginia]] with original members, his brother Sammie Sines & George Marshall.  In the early 1990's, band members had changed and the group recorded their first project "Crazy 'Bout Country" in a tobacco barn in [[Brookneal, Virginia]].  By 1994 the band had recorded their second project "Barstools & Guitars".  By 1998, he shifted from a band effort to a solo career.

=== 2001:  ''The Black #3 (A tribute to [[Dale Earnhardt]])'' ===

February 19, 2001 he wrote "The Black #3" (A tribute to [[Dale Earnhardt]]).  March 3, 2001 the song was recorded in [[Nashville, Tennessee]] on America's New Artist record label.  Sines was then signed to Music Row - Nashville & his CD would be distributed by [[Select-O-Hits]] out of [[Memphis, Tennessee]] on April 17, 2001.<ref name=Billboard> Billboard Magazine, [http://books.google.com/books?id=BBQEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA1&dq=billboard%20may%2010%202001&pg=PA77#v=twopage&q&f=false "The Black #3 Nationally Released"], May 5, 2001, online at Billboard Magazine</ref> A music video for "The Black #3" (A tribute to [[Dale Earnhardt]] was released and appeared on Great American Country Television.  Sines appeared in the August 7, 2001 print issue of Country Weekly as one of many country artist paying tribute to [[Dale Earnhardt]].<ref name=Billboard> Billboard Magazine, [http://www.countryweekly.com/news/stars-remember-earnhardt "STARS REMEMBER EARNHARDT "], August 7, 2001, Country Weekly Magazine</ref> He appeared in Country Music Live along side his team that created the music video for the [[Dale Earnhardt]] tribute. Sines had 4 national releases off this project, "The horse that they rode in on", "All she left me was alone", "The Black #3" (A tribute to [[Dale Earnhardt]]) & "keep loving this one".<ref name=BedfordBulletin> Bedford Bullettin, [http://www.bedfordbulletin.com/content/black-3 "Anniversary of Earnhardt<U+2019>s death fuels interest in local singer<U+2019>s recording"], February 23, 2011, online at Bedford Bulletin</ref> Sines appeared on Music City 103.3 [[WKDF]] with Carl P Mayfield in March 2001 and was invited on air to join the P Team at [[2001 NASCAR Busch Series]] inaugural Pepsi 300 was held April 14, 2014 at Nashville Superspeedway. [http://sections.lcni5.com/pdfs/030/2580.pdf] He was invited to appeared in June 2001 at Lupus 2001, in Orlando, Florida along side of [[Marc Anthony]], [[Lionel Richie]], [[Howie Dorough]] and the [[Backstreet Boys]] to support the Dorough Lupus Foundation.<ref> Backsteet.net, [http://www.backstreet.net/www.cgi?x=show&d=news&i=010505-0000-04&c=6e "Marc Anthony, Aaron Carter & More To Perform At Lupus 2001"], May 4, 2001, online at Backstree.net</ref><ref> Orlando Sentinel, [http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/2001-05-13/news/0105130105_1_dorough-lupus-individual-tickets "Dorough Lands Stars To Help Fight Lupus"], May 13, 2001, online at Orlando Sentinel</ref> In December 2002, he would be invited to appear with [[Sherman Hemsley]] on [[Carnival Cruise Lines]].<ref> Backsteet.net, [https://books.google.com/books?id=hjEDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA59&lpg=PA59&dq=Sherman+Hemsley+john+sines+jr&source=bl&ots=1ayy4T2MQl&sig=q2rGhno9PR5mWiv-cMIJRUJDgCQ&hl=en&sa=X&ei=EgDZVNWWGIO-ggTw-4KYCA&ved=0CCoQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=Sherman%20Hemsley%20john%20sines%20jr&f=false "Cruising With The Stars"], October, 2002, online at Cruise Travel</ref>

=== 2006:  ''Sines of Conviction'' ===

By 2006, he would write & record his first gospel CD and third studio project called "Sines of Conviction" recorded on his own label OMAR Records.  Three songs were released nationally from this project and reached the independent charts in [[Christian country music]]. "The man behind the hammer" would be his first release and would reached number four in 2007 and would be accompanied by a music video by the same name. His second release, "Live another day" would become his first number one single in August 2007.<ref> Powersource Music, [http://www.powersourcemusic.com/?page_id=5310 "'Live Another Day' Number 1, August 2007"], 2007, online at Powersource Music (By Rich Miller)</ref> His third single "Blinded Eyes" also reached number one in December 2007.<ref> Powersource Music, [http://www.powersourcemusic.com/?page_id=5301 "'Blinded Eyes' Number 1, December 2007"], 2007, online at Powersource Music (By Rich Miller)</ref> "Blinded Eyes" would also reach number one in Canada on [[Riverside Country]] in January & February 2008.<ref> Powersource Music, [http://www.riversidecountry.ca/content/chart/2008/01/top20-christian-country-chart-january-2008/ "'Blinded Eyes' Number 1 in Canada, January 2008"], January 2008, online at Riverside Country (By Jason Farris)</ref><ref> Powersource Music, [http://www.riversidecountry.ca/content/chart/2008/03/top20-christian-country-chart-february-2008/ "'Blinded Eyes' Number 1 in Canada, February 2008"], February 2008, online at Riverside Country (By Jason Farris)</ref> He was nominated by the [[Inspirational Country Music Association]] (ICMA) for Male Vocalist of the Year in 2007.<ref name=About.com> About.com, [http://christianmusic.about.com/od/awards/a/aa13thinspctry.htm "'John Sines, Jr' Nominated For 2007 Male Vocalist"], 2007, online at About.com (By Kim Jones)</ref>   "Blinded Eyes" was nominated as Song of the Year by the ICMA in 2008.<ref name=Christian News Wire> Christian New Wire, [http://www.christiannewswire.com/news/116967187.html "'Blinded Eyes' Nominated For 2008 Song Of The Year"], 2008, online at Christian News Wire (By Kim Dettwiller)</ref>  That same year the ICMA would also nominate him for Male Vocalist of the Year.<ref name=Christian News Wire> Christian New Wire, [http://www.christiannewswire.com/news/116967187.html "'John Sines, Jr' Nominated For 2008 Male Vocalist"], 2008, online at Christian News Wire (By Kim Dettwiller)</ref> As a result of his accomplishments in 2007, Sines would also appear on the cover of Powersource Magazine in August 2008.<ref> Powersource Magazine, [http://www.riversidecountry.ca/content/articles/2007/08/john-sines-jr-a-living-testimony/ "'John Sines, Jr' A Living Testimony"], August 11, 2008, online at Riverside Country (By Vickie Gardner)</ref> He also appeared on the nationally televised 13th Annual Inspirational Country Music Award Show (ICM's)  on November 4, 2007 at the Acuff Theater in Nashville as an award presenter for 'Vocal Group Of The Year' along side of [[Laura Bryna]] and Sue Allan Cooper.<ref> Standard Newswire, [http://www.standardnewswire.com/news/396711739.html/ "Performers and Presenters Added to the 2007 Inspirational Country Music Awards"], Added August 14, 2014, online at Standard Newswire (By Kim Dettwiller)</ref>

=== 2008:  ''ALIVE'' ===

In 2008, he recorded a live cd called "ALIVE" at Staunton River High School in [[Moneta, Virginia]].  "Walking with Jesus" would be the only release from this project. A music video for "Waiting on You" was recorded in front of a live crowd at Cattle Annie's in [[Lynchburg, Virginia]].

=== 2012:  ''Better Days'' ===

In 2012, he completed "Better Days". Although he has released no singles from this project at this time, "Sing, (In The Midnight Hour)" has become this hit on this project. The song was written after Sines heard evangelist [[David Ring]] preach a sermon on Acts 16.

=== 2014:  ''Sines Of The Season'' ===

In 2014, Sines recorded his first Christmas cd, "Sines Of The Season".

== Rock Pike Baptist Church ==

In June 2013 John became the pastor of Rock Pike Baptist Church in [[Forest, Virginia]].  He became an ordained minister in December 2013. 

== Music Ministry ==

Sines continues to travel as an evangelist to promote the Gospel of [[Jesus Christ]] through music.<ref> Cowboy Church, [http://www.roanoke.com/webmin/news/cowboy-church-reined-in/article_2566b7a4-e52c-5b80-9a3a-19117c766309.html "'Cowboy church' reined in"], May 12, 2006, online at The Roanoke Times</ref><ref> Hazel Kinder Lighthouse Theater, [http://eventful.com/columbia_mo/events/john-sines-jr-inspirational-country-concert-/E0-001-023133582-4 "John Sines Jr - Inspirational Country Concert  in Columbia"], September 5, 2009, online at Eventful</ref><ref> Bluetoad, [http://www.bluetoad.com/publication/?i=21682&p=30 "Inside Columbia Magazine Prime"], September 5, 2009, online at Inside Columbia Magazine</ref><ref> Cup-O-Joy, [http://www.greenbaynightlife.com/green-bay-events/index.php?com=detail&eID=19382 "John Sines, Jr at Cup O Joy in Green Bay"], August 16, 2013, online at Green Bay Nightlife</ref><ref> Lighthouse Ministry, [http://www.americantowns.com/wi/westbend/events/lighthouse-ministry-presents-music-movie-in-the-park-2013-08-17 "Lighthouse Ministry Presents: <U+201C>Music / Movie in the Park<U+201D>"], April 13, 2013, online at American Towns</ref><ref> Jacob's Well, [http://articles.courant.com/2014-04-13/community/hcrs-87875-eastern-connecticut-20140412_1_corner-drop-in-center-monthly-christian-nightclub-well-coffeehouse "Country Singer From Virginia Performing On May 2"], April 13, 2014, online at Hartford Courant</ref><ref> Jacob's Well Christian Coffeehouse, [http://patch.com/connecticut/vernon/jacobs-well-christian-coffeehouse_619bf768 "Country Singer From Virginia Performing On May 2"], April 12, 2014, online at Patch.com</ref> His unique connection with [[NASCAR]] and his outspoken stance for spreading the Gospel, has also attracted faith base related ministries such as Victory Weekend Ministries and Racing with Jesus Ministries.<ref> Bristol Motor Speedway,[http://www.bristolmotorspeedway.com/news_media/news_releases/bms-victory-weekend-ministries-offering-christian-entertainment-august.html "BMS, Victory Weekend Ministries Offering Christian Entertainment In August"], July 29, 2011, online at Bristol Motor Speedway</ref>[http://www.ministryupdates.org/rwjm/letters/l-3pj-pwfb.pdf]. Sines has also appeared on syndicated cable show "HIS Country Music" in Gilroy, California & "[[WPRZ-FM]] Praise Gathering and Concert" on "Virginia Living Television".<ref> HIS Country Music, [https://www.strongspace.com/cchm/public/archivevideo.html#TB_inline?height=240&width=320&inlineId=fp17 "Christian Country Helps Minstries"], June 2009, online at HIS Country Music Video Showcase</ref><ref> Virginia Living Television, [http://vimeo.com/101608021 "WPRZ Praise Gathering and Concert"], July 2014, online at Virginia Living Television</ref> Sines performs annually for the Amherst County Sheriffs Department to assist the D.A.R.E program.<ref>Christmas in Clifford, [http://www.newsadvance.com/new_era_progress/news/local/d-a-r-e-hosts-holiday-concert/article_2a974dec-ac9b-51ad-bc78-79868d4e7834.html "D.A.R.E. hosts holiday concert"], December 22, 2010, online at New Era Progress</ref> He has also appeared to help raise awareness for FASASD, Families Affected by Fetal Alcohol Spectrum Disorder. <ref>Families Affected by Fetal Alcohol Spectrum Disorder, [http://fafasd.org/announcements/ "CONCERT and FUNDRAISER"], February 1, 2013, online at FAFASD</ref> Sines also lends his talents to assist families in need.<ref>News Advance, [http://www.newsadvance.com/new_era_progress/news/local/amherst-county-mother-reflects-on--year-old-who-died/article_5dfb91c3-8bb9-56a6-b03b-8cfb735f84bf.html "Amherst County mother reflects on 8-year-old who died after asthma attack"], February 16, 2011, online at News Advance</ref><ref>WSET, [http://www.wset.com/story/21933862/madison-heights-woman-wont-fight-cancer-alone?clienttype=generic&mobilecgbypass "Madison Heights Woman Won't Fight Cancer Alone"], April 10, 2013, online at ABC13 - WSET</ref>
<ref>News Advance, [http://www.newsadvance.com/new_era_progress/news/music-event-to-benefit-deputy/article_603a0e14-0a77-11e3-93e3-001a4bcf6878.html "Music event to benefit deputy "], August 21, 2013, online at News Advance</ref>

